15. Short handoff summary for the agent

Build a clickable front-end prototype for a community-centered participation app. Use fake data. The core concept is not generic event browsing, but helping users orient through community, geography, time, and participation overlap. The signature experience should be a map/timeline explorer showing where and when community activity is happening, with clear explanations for why events or communities are relevant. Support three main modes: participant, facilitator, and community steward. Community dashboards should focus on opportunities and participation patterns rather than member lists. Facilitators should have rich profiles and be able to publish an event once and associate it with multiple communities. Include a mechanism for users to suggest an event as relevant to a community. Prioritize feel, legibility, overlap, and user experience over backend realism.